This paper is primarily focused on neural networks for image processing and computer vision, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the importance of loss functions in improving the quality of results, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories within computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel, differentiable error function, which is related to optimization and could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of loss functions on image restoration, which is a specific application of image processing and could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
